Description: Fragment of handle at neck join of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine grey-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 18 Name Ptolemaios. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0400.08
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1317)
